{"type":"message","id":"16aa28a9","parentId":"667d8ce2","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:42:04.846Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to respond to /start command. According to AGENTS.md, if BOOTSTRAP.md exists, follow it, then delete it. It doesn't exist, so we proceed.\n\nWe need to maybe introduce ourselves, check identity, maybe load IDENTITY.md, etc. The user sent /start, likely wants to start interaction. We should respond with a greeting and maybe ask what they need.\n\nBut we have to follow the guidelines: be helpful, resourceful. We can check the workspace for any existing files, maybe show what's there.\n\nLet's first list the workspace directory to see what's present. Use exec ls -la.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-bba2c67fbd774d07","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/asher/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":12280,"output":169,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12449,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778114519397,"responseId":"chatcmpl-bfe668f3001c4fbf"}}
