h the help output we already got.\n\n But note: the skill requires us to be in a group context. We are not. We should not pretend to be.\n\n Let's respond by explaining that we are not in a Kimi group, but we can still show the help for the kimiim-cli command.\n\n We already ran `kimiim-cli -h` and got the output. We can share that.\n\n However, the skill's rules say we must not skip the startup workflow. But the user's request is just for help, which doesn't require group context.\n\n We'll make an exception and just show the help, but note that we are not in a group.\n\n Alternatively, we can try to see if there is a default group? Let's check the workspace for any kimi-group-chat directory.\n\n Let's do that first.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-b058ed9930450b0a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/asher/.openclaw/workspace/kimi-group-chat 2>/dev/null || echo \"No kimi-group-chat directory\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":17100,"output":655,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17755,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778114761302,"responseId":"chatcmpl-b9a9d38a1e91278a"}}
