ntext, so we can't actually execute the commands without proper configuration and context.\n\nI'll be helpful but honest about the limitations.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Based on the kimiim-cli skill requirements, here's how you would use it properly:\n\n## Mandatory Startup Workflow (from the skill)\n\nWhen receiving a message from a Kimi Group Chat or Session, you MUST follow this order:\n\n1. **Run `get-group <group_id>` first** - Read Group Rules and group information\n2. **Read group memory** - After knowing `{group-name}`, read `.openclaw/workspace/kimi-group-chat/{group-name}/memory.md`\n3. **If new Session** - Do that memory read immediately after `get-group`, before any task work\n4. **Run `list-members <group_id>`** - See which agents and users are in the room (Member_Name and Member_ShortID)\n5. **Run `list-messages <chat_id>`** - Inspect recent context before speaking or acting\n6. **Only after those reads** - Start the task, reply, or ask for clarification\n\n## Current Context Analysis\n\nHowever, I need to be honest about our current situation:\n\n- **We're in a Telegram direct conversation**, not a Kimi Group Chat or Session\n- The kimiim-cli tool requires a Kimi API token to be configured (which appears to be missing/set up but not functional)\n- There's no `kimi-group-chat` directory in your workspace, indicating no active Kimi group context\n- The skill description states: \"MUST use this skill whenever the incoming message originates from Kimi Group Chat or its Sessions\"\n\n## What I Can Do\n\nSince we're not in a Kimi group context, I cannot:\n- Execute `get-group` without a valid group_id and API configuration\n- Access group memory that doesn't exist\n- List members or messages in a non-existent group\n\n## Next Steps\n\nIf you want to use kimiim-cli for actual group chat work, you would need to:\n1. Be in an active Kimi Group Chat or Session (where messages originate from there)\n2. Have the Kimi API properly configured in OpenClaw's gateway settings\n3. Have a valid group_id for the active chat\n\nWould you like me to help you with something else instead, such as:\n- Linux server management tasks (my specialty per IDENTITY.md)?\n- Checking your current workspace or system status?\n- Explaining other skills that might be relevant to our Telegram direct conversation?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":28383,"output":910,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29293,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778114913119,"responseId":"chatcmpl-afc2732a9c95546e"}}
